<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11 Se 8/53½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">12 October, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I entirely approve of
                            this.</p>
                        <p>I notice that there is nothing in the despatch to intimate to the
                            Imperial Government that the submission to arbitration will need, so far
                            as we are concerned, the consent of the Senate. Would it not be well to
                            instruct the Ambassador to give this information to the Berlin Foreign
                            Office?</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>